"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648826","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-06","<p>In addition to independent evaluations of CDC’s impact that have been and will be undertaken, DFID are currently in the design stages of a complex new fifteen-year study to generate more detailed longitudinal data on the development impacts of CDC investments. We are the first Government ever to conduct such an in-depth study into their development finance institution. In order to assure we get the best value for money, this study will go through a comprehensive and competitive tendering process. It is anticipated that this study be tendered for in the first half of 2017.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-12-06T13:16:43.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648826/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648826/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-30","Commonwealth Development Corporation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, when the evaluation contract for the Commonwealth Development Corporation Group outlined in the 2015 business case for recapitalisation will be set.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","55650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648827","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-07","<p>Core contributions to the multilateral finance institutions for 2010-2015 are set out in the table attached. UK Official Development Assistance (ODA) to multilateral finance institutions is scored as ODA at the point at which the funding is provided to them.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-12-07T18:16:01.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648827/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648827/answer","55651.docx","55651.docx","55651","55651","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648827/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-30","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the value was of all official development assistance scorable investments in each of the multilateral development finance institutions in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","55651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648828","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-06","<p>DFID has supported the current election process in the Democratic Republic of Congo since 2015, focussing on increasing democratic representation of women and youth, protecting human rights defenders and broadening the Catholic Church’s electoral observation activities. In early 2016, DFID announced that additional funding of £6.6million could be made available to support the Electoral Commission in updating the electoral register. These funds are available if and only if the Congolese authorities show political will to hold free and fair elections.</p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-12-06T16:17:01.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648828/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648828/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-30","Democratic Republic of Congo: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether her Department plans to provide financial or technical assistance to the Democratic Republic of Congo to ensure that elections in line with the 2006 constitution take place.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","55643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648829","Department for International Development","false","2016-12-05","<p>In 2014, CDC provided DFID with an Offering Memorandum setting out the case for and requesting additional capital in the amount of £735m. In accordance with the Share Subscription agreement signed in July 2015, DFID has provided CDC with two tranches of additional capital funding: £450 million in 2015 and a further £285 million in 2016. In total these amount to £735 million.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-12-05T18:07:32.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648829/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648829/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-30","Commonwealth Development Corporation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what requests for capital funding were received by her Department from the Commonwealth Development Corporation/CDC Group in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","55702"
