"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648869","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-08","<p>The Department for Transport is supportive of increasing the number of car parking spaces at stations where possible.</p><p> </p><p>The current Northern franchise agreement contains a commitment for the franchisee to provide 250 additional car park spaces across its estate at specific named stations. Whilst none of those stations affected by the increase are those named above, the franchisee has the discretion to carry out improvements at alternative stations, should any of those covered by the initial commitment prove unworkable.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-08T13:40:55.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648869/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648869/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-30","Railway Stations: West Yorkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to improve parking arrangements and provision at Brighouse, Mytholmroyd, Hebden Bridge and Todmorden railway stations.","false","Biography information for Craig Whittaker","Calder Valley","Craig Whittaker","55604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648870","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-08","<p>Over the last year, Network Rail’s spend on labour services with those companies listed breaks down as follows:</p><p>(a) £21,355,662.89</p><p>(b) £22,679,386.19</p><p>(c) £20,064,419.53</p><p>(d) £10,755,465.70</p><p>(e) Network Rail does not hold this information.<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup></p><p> </p><p><sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup> Network Rail assumes that all spends with the named contractors are direct.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-08T13:36:50.967Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648870/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648870/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648870/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-30","Network Rail: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much Network Rail has spent on labour services from (a) Ganymede Solutions, (b) McGinley Support Services (Infrastructure), (c) Morson Human Resources, (d) Shorterm and (e) each of those company's subsidiaries in the last year.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","55570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648871","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-08","<p>The Department has not undertaken such an assessment.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-08T13:18:26.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648871/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/648871/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-30","Railways: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the extent of the use of (a) zero hours contracts, (b) bogus self-employment and (c) guaranteed minimum hours contracts in Network Rail's supply chain.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","55540"
