"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647958","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>The UK is well placed to deal with the challenges, and take advantage of the opportunities, that lie ahead as this nation makes a success of Brexit.</p><p>The Civil Service is focused on delivering this Government’s commitment to leave the EU and get the very best deal for the UK. We are equipping ourselves with the right people and the right skills across government to make this happen.</p>",,"Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen",,"2016-12-12T14:07:27.043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647958/answer","Biography information for Baroness Chisholm of Owlpen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647958/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-11-29","Brexit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment has been made of the current levels of Civil Service personnel and of their ability to manage the Brexit process.","false","Biography information for Baroness Smith of Basildon",,"Baroness Smith of Basildon","HL3655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647959","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Steering Group is chaired by the chief executives of GSK and AstraZeneca and includes the Wellcome Trust and a range of life sciences trade associations (the Association of British Healthcare Industries, Association of the British Pharmaceutical Industry, BioIndustry Association), representing both large and small UK life sciences companies across the various business areas that make up the sector. The Group’s first meeting was on 6 September and it met again on 23 November with further dates yet to be set. The Group has engaged widely with stakeholders across the UK life sciences sector on subjects including regulation, trade and investment and access to finance.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-12-12T15:02:18.83Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647959/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647959/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-29","UK EU Life Sciences Transition Programme Steering Group","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer by Baroness Neville-Rolfe on 21 November (HL Deb, col 1725) concerning the UK EU Life Sciences Steering group, (1) who are the members of the group, (2) when it first met, (3) when further meetings are expected to take place, and (4) with which stakeholders the group have been engaging.","false","Biography information for Baroness Smith of Basildon",,"Baroness Smith of Basildon","HL3656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647960","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-06","<p>In the Autumn Statement, we announced an investment of an extra £2 billion a year in R&amp;D by the end of this Parliament. We will set out the breakdown of the funding in due course. The delivery mechanisms for this investment are currently being worked through.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-12-06T15:55:03.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647960/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647960/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-29","Research: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer by Baroness Neville-Rolfe on 21 November (HL Deb, col 1727), whether the funding to support research and development will be delivered through the research councils.","false","Biography information for Baroness Smith of Basildon",,"Baroness Smith of Basildon","HL3657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647961","Department of Health","false","2016-12-12","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-12-12T12:23:00.17Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647961/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/647961/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-29","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what percentage of children and young people referred to child and adolescent mental health services in England were not allocated a service in 2015–16; and what proportion of the cases in which a service was not allocated resulted from (1) lack of available trained staff, (2) lack of funding, and (3) both.","false","Biography information for Baroness Fall",,"Baroness Fall","HL3658"
